Wanted by cops Multimedia    ·   User Galleries   ·   News in Pictures
	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Harare Saps are looking for a man who might assist them in solving a case of fraud and attempted murder. Police believe that this man (pictured below) could assist them in solving the cases of fraudulent acts of selling houses that don’t exist. According to police spokesperson Captain Siyabulela Vukubi, the houses were allegedly sold to a number of unsuspecting victims, who were not aware it was scam. “The victims went as far as applying for loans through the banks and transferred the cash into the suspect’s account. In one instance, the suspect allegedly fired shots at a victim who went to demand the money that was fraudulently taken from them. Fortunately the victim was unharmed,” he said. The police are investigating the cases of fraud and attempted murder. Vukubi urged anyone who may have information with regards to the whereabouts of this man in the picture is requested to contact Harare SAPS at (021) 363 9000 or I O D/ Sgt Mpho Mdaka at 084 804 7606. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  